The global spinach market is expected to witness substantial growth between 2022 and 2029. Spinach has gained popularity due to its various health benefits, including being a rich source of vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants. The market is segmented based on form, distribution channel, and end use. In terms of form, the market is categorized into fresh, frozen, canned, and others. The fresh segment is likely to dominate the market due to the increasing demand for fresh produce among consumers. By distribution channel, the market is segmented into supermarkets/hypermarkets, specialty stores, online retail, and others. The supermarkets/hypermarkets segment is anticipated to hold a significant market share as these outlets offer a wide range of spinach varieties to consumers. In the end use segment, the market is divided into household, food service industry, and food processing industry.

